race.comment: SAVAGERY VIBE (12) has had two runs since joining the Tony Gollan stable, filling a minor placing on each occasion. Motored home to get up for third at the end of 1000m behind the smart Larado last start. Perfectly placed out to this trip third-up and is poised to open her Queensland account. CHEVAL CHIC (6) was edged out when resuming in a similar race to this two starts back. Disappointed at Doomben last time out a month ago and has been freshened up. In the right race to bounce back to form. JUST PRECIOUS (9) just failed to hold out SAVAGERY VIBE in the battle for third when they clashed over 1000m here recently. That was her first run for four months and 1200m is more her go. Can improve enough to test this field. BLUE SPINEL (4) hasn't won for two years but she is racing well, including a near miss in a midweeker at Doomben last time. Each-way option. LUNAR EIGHT (13) returned from a long spell in good order at the Gold Coast last start. Likely improver.
